## Triage: `refresh_survives_401` failure

**Root cause** — `src/auth/session.rs`, `retry_after_401`:

```rust
fn retry_after_401(&mut self) {
    return;                        // <-- unconditional early return
    self.reauth_with_cached_grant();  // dead code, never runs
}
```

The function returns immediately, so `reauth_with_cached_grant()` is never executed. By the time anything else looks at the session, the cached grant has been dropped and re-auth never happens — which is exactly what `tests/session_test.rs::refresh_survives_401` asserts against.

**Proposed fix** — remove the stray `return;` so the re-auth call actually runs:

```rust
fn retry_after_401(&mut self) {
    self.reauth_with_cached_grant();
}
```

That should turn the test green. The change looks trivial, but I'm flagging rather than committing it: my delegation here is **read + comment only** — I don't have write access to the repo, so applying it myself isn't something I'm authorized (or able) to do. Could a maintainer with push rights apply the one-line change above? Worth a quick glance to confirm `reauth_with_cached_grant()` has no other side effects that the early-return was (intentionally or not) masking before merging.
